#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn35.92"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.92:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.92:0.2"
msgid "9. Channavagga "
msgstr "9. With Channa "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn35.92:0.3"
msgid "92. Paṭhamadvayasutta "
msgstr "92. A Duality (1st) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn35.92:1.1"
msgid "“Dvayaṃ vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, I will teach you a duality. "

msgctxt "sn35.92:1.2"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha. "
msgstr "Listen … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.92:1.3"
msgid "Kiñca, bhikkhave, dvayaṃ? "
msgstr "And what is a duality? "

msgctxt "sn35.92:1.4"
msgid "Cakkhuñceva rūpā ca, sotañceva saddā ca, ghānañceva gandhā ca, jivhā ceva rasā ca, kāyo ceva phoṭṭhabbā ca, mano ceva dhammā ca—"
msgstr "It’s just the eye and sights, the ear and sounds, the nose and smells, the tongue and tastes, the body and touches, and the mind and thoughts. "

msgctxt "sn35.92:1.5"
msgid "idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dvayaṃ. "
msgstr "This is called a duality. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn35.92:2.1"
msgid "Yo, bhikkhave, evaṃ vadeyya: "
msgstr "Mendicants, suppose someone was to say: "

msgctxt "sn35.92:2.2"
msgid "‘ahametaṃ dvayaṃ paccakkhāya aññaṃ dvayaṃ paññapessāmī’ti, tassa vācāvatthukamevassa. "
msgstr "‘I’ll reject this duality and describe another duality.’ They’d have no grounds for that, "

msgctxt "sn35.92:2.3"
msgid "Puṭṭho ca na sampāyeyya. "
msgstr "they’d be stumped by questions, and, in addition, they’d get frustrated. "

msgctxt "sn35.92:2.4"
msgid "Uttariñca vighātaṃ āpajjeyya. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.92:2.5"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "sn35.92:2.6"
msgid "Yathā taṃ, bhikkhave, avisayasmin”ti. "
msgstr "Because they’re out of their element.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.92:2.7"
msgid "Navamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
